[SN]TITLE[SN]
Jonathon Thomas Swansea death: Daniel Shepherd in court

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A man has appeared in court charged with manslaughter after a reveller died following an incident in Swansea in the early hours of Sunday.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Former Swansea RFC player Jonathan Thomas, 34, was taken to Morriston Hospital where he later died.
Daniel Jason Shepherd, 23, from Skewen, Neath Port Talbot, spoke to confirm his details and was remanded in custody at Swansea Magistrates' Court on Tuesday.
He will appear at the city's crown court on 13 November.
